About the Company
Our Client is a global provider of managed network solutions with offices in all the major cities in the world.
Responsibilities
We're looking for a driven and professional Channel Sales Account Manager to be part of a growing sales team, growing the company's revenue and building brand awareness within the connectivity industry in the Asia Pacific region.
Manage assigned channel partners and identify new business opportunities to grow their accounts;
Generate new business through prospecting and bringing onboard new accounts;
Build relationships and connections with prospective C-level or executive stakeholders to identify business and sales opportunities;
Provide consultative sales pitches to articulate the company's positioning of its services;
Understand the market, including trends and developments, and competitors offerings;
Work with pre-sales and engineering teams to deliver the right products for clients;
Promote and upsell other products within the company's portfolio;
Achieve targeted new business revenues
Prepare sales reports and forecasts as required.
Requirements
Tertiary education in any discipline, preferably in business management;
At least 5 years of experience in a similar role;
Strong understanding of the telecommunications and internetworking ecosystem;
Proven track record of meeting and exceeding sales targets;
Good business acumen and strong professionalism;
Perseverance, flexibility and results-orientation;
Strong customer-centric mindset, excellent client relationship skills and executive rapport;
Excellent communication skills, including presentation and negotiation skills;
Strong command of English language, and proficiency in any other regional language would be an advantage.
Employment Details
Some regional travel is required for this role;
Dynamic, fast-paced environment;
Attractive remuneration, with on-target-earnings, and additional benefits.
Get in touch with us
If you'd like to explore this opportunity, please reach out to Kathy Tang (Regn No. R21101933) at [HIDDEN TEXT] for a confidential discussion.
