Job Description
The candidate is to reinforce the expertise on the existing AMUNDI-ITS network security solutions.
To deal with migration projects, upgrades of various platforms, and to ensure their daily support, the candidate will need to:
- Acquire deep knowledge about the infrastructures in place and their evolution;
- Build the related action plans with the network/security team;
- Propose architectures, install, deploy, configure or reconfigure existing network and firewall architectures;
- Support the current network solutions and service offerings;
- Provide technical support to the operations, server and application teams;
- Deliver and support network infrastructure projects, including topics like: WAN, LAN optimization, security requirements deployment, new sites implementation, etc.;
- Create standard documentation, from physical and logical architecture diagrams to process and procedures;
- Provide good solid support to current IT groups and the business itself.
Requirements - Technical Knowledge
The ideal candidate should have strong knowledge of the following technologies:
- F5 components (load balancers, remote APM, WAF)
- BlueCoat Proxy Equipment, Palo Alto
- Firewall internet (Fortinet), FW office (firepower cisco), FW Datacenter (firepower cisco)
- Routing (BGP)
- Switching (STP)
- WiFi (Cisco WLC/ISE/AP)
- Network tools (Cacti / Solarwinds /.)
Added advantages
- Experience in Cloud infrastructure / implementation
He/She should have:
- Degree in IT;
- At least 8 years relevant experience;
- Expertise in Network and Security environments;
- Ability to work in a team and with multiple teams;
- Knowledge of ITIL processes;
- Proficiency in English (spoken & written).

About the Company
Our Client is a leading provider of supply chain management solutions.
Responsibilities
We're looking for a customer-centric Senior / Solutions Architect to be responsible for high-level designs for integrated logistics solutions that are aligned with principles of information technology architecture.
Conduct feasibility studies to analyse demands based on customers requirements as well as technical standards and principles;
Perform cost reviews and optimization by reducing risks and ensuring regulatory compliance;
Evaluate performance of solutions designed, including security, audit and tracking considerations;
Ensure that solution principles and concepts are aligned within the organisation;
Work with various technical specialists and stakeholders to ensure a smooth delivery of solutions.
Requirements
Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems Engineering or other relevant discipline;
Certifications in enterprise architecture methodology or other relevant qualifications;
At least 5 to 8 years of experience in a technical solutioning role;
Track record of enterprise solution design and delivery;
Strong understanding of cloud technologies including Microsoft Azure and Amazon Web Services;
Understanding of IT governance and strategy;
Ability to multi-task and oversee several projects at the same time;
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills;
Excellent communication skills and customer-centric mindset.
Employment Details
Permanent role;
Work location: East Singapore;
Excellent work environment with attractive remuneration and benefits.
